SIMPLE: excellent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excellent
<hw>Ex"cel*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>excellent</ets>, L. <ets>excellens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr.
of <ets>excellere</ets>. See <er>Excel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Excelling; surpassing others in some good quality or the sum of
qualities; of great worth; eminent, in a good sense; superior; <as>as,
an <ex>excellent</ex> man, artist, citizen, husband, discourse, book,
song, etc.; <ex>excellent</ex> breeding, principles, aims,
action.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To love . . . ⟦br⟧
What I see <qex>excellent</qex> in good or fair.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Superior in kind or degree, irrespective of moral
quality; -- used with words of a bad significance.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Ironical]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>excellent</xex> hypocrite.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hume.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their sorrows are most <qex>excellent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Worthy; choice; prime; valuable; select;
exquisite; transcendent; admirable; worthy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excellent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Excellent
<hw>Ex"cel*lent</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Excellently; eminently;
exceedingly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧This comes off well and
<xex>excellent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excellently</ent>⟦br⟧
